{"search_data": "CentralDynamic Flexi Fare Scheme in Indian Railways \u2013 Discount on Tickets PricesDynamic Flexi Fare SchemeThe important features and highlights of this scheme are as follows:-Discounted Fares \u2013 In case the seats are vacant in Railways or trains are not fully booked, then passengers will get discounted fares. Moreover, govt. will also provide discounts on the routes where occupancy is relatively low.Dynamic Pricing \u2013 Subsequently, this scheme follows dynamic pricing policy just like hotels. In this scheme, firstly the prices are low, then prices go high and then passengers will get discounts on the remaining seats.Remove Limitations of Flexi-Fare Scheme \u2013 In flexi fare scheme, the base fares rises from 10% to 50% with every 10% of berths booked. Moreover, this scheme increases the revenue but the railways lost its several passengers. So to increase the number of passengers, govt. will launch dynamic flexi fare scheme.Flexibility in Rates \u2013 This dynamic fare scheme will provide flexibility in the prices during peak season, lean season. Moreover, citizens will get discounted fares on weekdays, weekends or festivals.Utilization of Assets \u2013 Central govt. is making plans for maximum utilization of the assets. Besides the original journey, trains can also be utilized for a small trip in the free time or through reducing the time for maintenance."}